title: Google\Cloud\Dataproc\V1\GceClusterConfig
name: GceClusterConfig
description:
Common config settings for resources of Google Compute Engine cluster instances, applicable to all instances in the cluster.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dataproc.v1.GceClusterConfig

Extends \Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.zone_uri
params.description: Optional. The zone where the Google Compute Engine cluster will be located. On a create request, it is required in the "global" region. If omitted in a non-global Cloud Dataproc region, the service will pick a zone in the corresponding Compute Engine region. On a get request, zone will always be present. A full URL, partial URI, or short name are valid. Examples: https://www.googleapis.com/compute/v1/projects/[project_id]/zones/[zone] projects/[project_id]/zones/[zone] * us-central1-f

params.name: data.network_uri
params.description: Optional. The Google Compute Engine network to be used for machine communications. Cannot be specified with subnetwork_uri. If neither network_uri nor subnetwork_uri is specified, the "default" network of the project is used, if it exists. Cannot be a "Custom Subnet Network" (see Using Subnetworks for more information). A full URL, partial URI, or short name are valid. Examples: https://www.googleapis.com/compute/v1/projects/[project_id]/regions/global/default projects/[project_id]/regions/global/default * default

params.name: data.subnetwork_uri
params.description: Optional. The Google Compute Engine subnetwork to be used for machine communications. Cannot be specified with network_uri. A full URL, partial URI, or short name are valid. Examples: https://www.googleapis.com/compute/v1/projects/[project_id]/regions/us-east1/sub0 projects/[project_id]/regions/us-east1/sub0 * sub0

params.name: data.internal_ip_only
params.description: Optional. If true, all instances in the cluster will only have internal IP addresses. By default, clusters are not restricted to internal IP addresses, and will have ephemeral external IP addresses assigned to each instance. This internal_ip_only restriction can only be enabled for subnetwork enabled networks, and all off-cluster dependencies must be configured to be accessible without external IP addresses.

params.name: data.service_account
params.description: Optional. The service account of the instances. Defaults to the default Google Compute Engine service account. Custom service accounts need permissions equivalent to the folloing IAM roles: roles/logging.logWriter roles/storage.objectAdmin (see https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/access/service-accounts#custom_service_accounts for more information). Example: [account_id]@[project_id].iam.gserviceaccount.com

params.name: data.service_account_scopes
params.description: Optional. The URIs of service account scopes to be included in Google Compute Engine instances. The following base set of scopes is always included: https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud.useraccounts.readonly https://www.googleapis.com/auth/devstorage.read_write https://www.googleapis.com/auth/logging.write If no scopes are specified, the following defaults are also provided: https://www.googleapis.com/auth/bigquery https://www.googleapis.com/auth/bigtable.admin.table https://www.googleapis.com/auth/bigtable.data * https://www.googleapis.com/auth/devstorage.full_control

params.name: data.tags
params.description: The Google Compute Engine tags to add to all instances (see Tagging instances).

params.name: data.metadata
params.description: The Google Compute Engine metadata entries to add to all instances (see Project and instance metadata).

methods.name: getServiceAccount
methods.description:
Optional. The service account of the instances. Defaults to the default Google Compute Engine service account. Custom service accounts need permissions equivalent to the folloing IAM roles:

  • roles/logging.logWriter
  • roles/storage.objectAdmin (see https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/access/service-accounts#custom_service_accounts for more information).

Example: [account_id]@[project_id].iam.gserviceaccount.com
